Laluaua<br>
52 Pal HOF <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CBC6B1><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ukordail.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kordail</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(9/28/00 2:54:58 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Fear</span><hr size=1> I had a blast, for the most part - fighting nasy lag, and several linkdeaths were the only real problem. I would like to bring something up tho.. in the event there has been connection problems, not just for one person, but server-wide (like we experienced that day) is it possible for each member of each class to actually know who from thier class is on the raid? This may help cut down on the chance of someone not getting to roll on an item they can use because of LD.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uhindrud.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Hindrud</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(9/28/00 4:42:19 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/SiliconValley/Bridge/5468/dogdrinking_sm_wht.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Fear</span><hr size=1> Kordail, if you type in eg.   /who shaman.    This will list all the shaman in your zone at the time.  If there annon, they will not show up.<br>
<br>
/who Druid<br>
/who cleric<br>
<br>
etc...<br>
<br>
Hope this is answered your question bro, cya around.<br>
<br>
Hin <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CBC6B1><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ukordail.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kordail</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(10/1/00 1:36:50 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Fear</span><hr size=1> did that, Hindrud <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ucassia.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cassia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(10/1/00 3:13:26 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Fear</span><hr size=1> I think, Hindrud, he was suggesting that everyone have a list, so that when there's something to be lottoed, link dead people can be included.  Obviously, if you've gone link dead and aren't in the game, you won't show up on a /who cleric.  /bonk Hindrud. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CBC6B1><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ulaluana.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Laluana</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(10/2/00 10:49:05 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> who all on</span><hr size=1> Something we can all do individually with the /who cleric ect is to make our own list up at the beginning and periodically check it and update it. That way we all know who is there or not. Easy to manage for us all individually. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uhindrud.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Hindrud</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(10/2/00 3:52:39 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/SiliconValley/Bridge/5468/dogdrinking_sm_wht.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Fear</span><hr size=1> Its always such a pleasure hearing from you Cassia.  Maybe I just read Kordail's posting the wrong way.  IMO, I think everyone attending the hunt acted very adult like and professional.  Whenever someone died, or went LD, someone in there party always shouted, or /ooc that the person was out.  Please Bonk me some more, I love it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CBC6B1><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uplangstrump.showPublicProfile?language=EN>P Langstrump</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(10/2/00 4:55:48 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www3.sympatico.ca/seyil/villa/pippirun.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Fear</span><hr size=1> People overall were VERY courteous at the raid. And what wasn't courteous enough was pretty much yelled ...err, voiced pretty quickly &gt;)<br>
<br>
I think the concern Kordail had was the fact that LD people who have been there during the entire raid but go LD at one point do not get a shot at those drops.  Although a bit tedious, but I think it is fair to expect us to remember those that went LD when rolling for an item, be it by an official list, be it by group members being responsible for keeping track of the person who went LD (and also what class s/he is).  I admit, most of my time at the raid was spend reading everything that scrolled by me in lightspeed and paying little attention to the drops <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  , but I will try to be more aware next time. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uplangstrump.showPublicProfile?language=EN>P Langstrump</A> at: 10/2/00 5:12:01 pm<br></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildscogplanesraidschedule.showMessage?topicID=40.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildscogplanesraidschedule.showMessage?topicID=34.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildscogplanesraidschedule.emailToFriend?topicID=36.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildscogplanesraidschedule.threadControl?topicID=36.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/far_east/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildscogplanesraidschedule.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=36.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of 